 first ‘.’\n:   colon\n\\W  the basename of the current working directory, with $HOME abbreviated with a tilde\n    white space\n\\u  the username of the current user\n\\$  if the effective UID is 0, a #, otherwise a $\n    white space\n'   single quote\n\nExamples:\n\nMacBookPro:~ user$\nMacBookPro:Documents user$\nMacBookPro:~ root#\n",[55],[153],{"type":42,"tag":58,"props":154,"children":155},{"__ignoreMap":6},[156],{"type":47,"value":150},{"type":42,"tag":76,"props":158,"children":160},{"id":159},"my-preference",[161],{"type":47,"value":162},"My preference",{"type":42,"tag":43,"props":164,"children":165},{},[166,168,174,176,181,183,189],{"type":47,"value":167},"I personally use ",{"type":42,"tag":58,"props":169,"children":171},{"className":170},[],[172],{"type":47,"value":173},"PS1=''",{"type":47,"value":175}," within my ",{"type":42,"tag":58,"props":177,"children":179},{"className":178},[],[180],{"type":47,"value":110},{"type":47,"value":182}," file. This provides a blank prompt which feels good to me. If I ever get lost, I type a quick ",{"type":42,"tag":58,"props":184,"children":186},{"className":185},[],[187],{"type":47,"value":188},"pwd",{"type":47,"value":190}," to see where I am, but I rarely run into that problem.",{"type":42,"tag":43,"props":192,"children":193},{},[194],{"type":47,"value":195},"And cmon, this looks great!",{"type":42,"tag":197,"props":198,"children":205},"img",{"src":199,"alt":200,"className":201},"https://codybontecou.com/images/clean-terminal.png","Screenshot of my terminal",[202,203,204],"mt-6","rounded-lg","shadow-lg",[],{"title":6,"searchDepth":207,"depth":207,"links":208},2,[209,210],{"id":78,"depth":207,"text":81},{"id":159,"depth":207,"text":162},"markdown","content:hide-username-on-mac-terminal-prompt.md","content","hide-username-on-mac-terminal-prompt.md","md",1732285114283]